 if hell is expanding at a rate faster than the increase of souls in hell , then the temperature and pressure will drop until hell freezes over . ^ so which is it ? ^ if we accept the postulate given to me by ms.  ame  ame during my freshman year , ( ... that it will be a cold day in hell before i sleep with you ) , and take into account the fact that i still have not succeeded in having sexual relations with her , then , #  um cannot be true , and thus i am sure that hell is exothermic and will not freeze . ^ the student received the only a given . </text_normal></message_body></message>